{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm extremely excited to be given the opportunity"},{"time":3000,"text":"to come and speak to you today"},{"time":5000,"text":"about what I consider to be"},{"time":7000,"text":"the biggest stunt on Earth."},{"time":10000,"text":"Or perhaps not quite on Earth."},{"time":12000,"text":"A parachute jump from the very edge of space."},{"time":16000,"text":"More about that a bit later on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18000,"text":"What I'd like to do first is take you through"},{"time":20000,"text":"a very brief helicopter ride of stunts"},{"time":23000,"text":"and the stunts industry in the movies and in television,"},{"time":26000,"text":"and show you how technology"},{"time":28000,"text":"has started to interface with the physical skills"},{"time":30000,"text":"of the stunt performer"},{"time":32000,"text":"in a way that makes the stunts bigger"},{"time":35000,"text":"and actually makes them safer than they've ever been before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"I've been a professional stunt man for 13 years."},{"time":42000,"text":"I'm a stunt coordinator. And as well as perform stunts"},{"time":44000,"text":"I often design them."},{"time":46000,"text":"During that time, health and safety has become everything about my job."},{"time":49000,"text":"It's critical now that when a car crash happens"},{"time":53000,"text":"it isn't just the stunt person we make safe, it's the crew."},{"time":56000,"text":"We can't be killing camera men. We can't be killing stunt men."},{"time":58000,"text":"We can't be killing anybody or hurting anybody on set,"},{"time":60000,"text":"or any passerby. So, safety is everything."},{"time":63000,"text":"But it wasn't always that way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"In the old days of the silent movies --"},{"time":68000,"text":"Harold Lloyd here, hanging famously from the clock hands --"},{"time":72000,"text":"a lot of these guys did their own stunts. They were quite remarkable."},{"time":74000,"text":"They had no safety, no real technology."},{"time":77000,"text":"What safety they had was very scant."},{"time":80000,"text":"This is the first stunt woman,"},{"time":82000,"text":"Rosie Venger, an amazing woman."},{"time":84000,"text":"You can see from the slide, very very strong."},{"time":86000,"text":"She really paved the way"},{"time":88000,"text":"at a time when nobody was doing stunts, let alone women."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"My favorite and a real hero of mine is Yakima Canutt."},{"time":94000,"text":"Yakima Canutt really formed the stunt fight."},{"time":98000,"text":"He worked with John Wayne and most of those old punch-ups you see"},{"time":101000,"text":"in the Westerns. Yakima was either there or he stunt coordinated."},{"time":104000,"text":"This is a screen capture from \"Stagecoach,\""},{"time":106000,"text":"where Yakima Canutt is doing one of the most dangerous stunts I've ever seen."},{"time":110000,"text":"There is no safety, no back support,"},{"time":112000,"text":"no pads, no crash mats, no sand pits in the ground."},{"time":115000,"text":"That's one of the most dangerous horse stunts, certainly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"Talking of dangerous stunts and bringing things slightly up to date,"},{"time":121000,"text":"some of the most dangerous stunts we do as stunt people are fire stunts."},{"time":125000,"text":"We couldn't do them without technology."},{"time":127000,"text":"These are particularly dangerous"},{"time":129000,"text":"because there is no mask on my face."},{"time":131000,"text":"They were done for a photo shoot. One for the Sun newspaper,"},{"time":133000,"text":"one for FHM magazine."},{"time":135000,"text":"Highly dangerous, but also you'll notice"},{"time":137000,"text":"it doesn't look as though I'm wearing anything underneath the suit."},{"time":139000,"text":"The fire suits of old, the bulky suits, the thick woolen suits,"},{"time":142000,"text":"have been replaced with modern materials"},{"time":145000,"text":"like Nomex or, more recently, Carbonex --"},{"time":148000,"text":"fantastic materials that enable us as stunt professionals"},{"time":150000,"text":"to burn for longer, look more spectacular, and in pure safety."},{"time":154000,"text":"Here's a bit more."},{"time":158000,"text":"There's a guy with a flame thrower there, giving me what for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"One of the things that a stuntman often does,"},{"time":163000,"text":"and you'll see it every time in the big movies,"},{"time":165000,"text":"is be blown through the air."},{"time":167000,"text":"Well, we used to use trampettes. In the old days, that's all they had."},{"time":170000,"text":"And that's a ramp. Spring off the thing and fly through the air,"},{"time":172000,"text":"and hopefully you make it look good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"Now we've got technology. This thing is called an air ram."},{"time":177000,"text":"It's a frightening piece of equipment for the novice stunt performer,"},{"time":180000,"text":"because it will break your legs very, very quickly"},{"time":182000,"text":"if you land on it wrong."},{"time":184000,"text":"Having said that, it works with compressed nitrogen."},{"time":187000,"text":"And that's in the up position. When you step on it,"},{"time":189000,"text":"either by remote control or with the pressure of your foot,"},{"time":191000,"text":"it will fire you, depending on the gas pressure,"},{"time":193000,"text":"anything from five feet to 30 feet."},{"time":196000,"text":"I could, quite literally, fire myself into the gallery."},{"time":200000,"text":"Which I'm sure you wouldn't want."},{"time":202000,"text":"Not today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":204000,"text":"Car stunts are another area"},{"time":206000,"text":"where technology and engineering"},{"time":208000,"text":"advances have made life easier for us, and safer."},{"time":211000,"text":"We can do bigger car stunts than ever before now."},{"time":213000,"text":"Being run over is never easy."},{"time":215000,"text":"That's an old-fashioned, hard, gritty, physical stunt."},{"time":218000,"text":"But we have padding, and fantastic shock-absorbing things like Sorbothane --"},{"time":222000,"text":"the materials that help us, when we're hit like this,"},{"time":225000,"text":"not to hurt ourselves too much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"The picture in the bottom right-hand corner there"},{"time":230000,"text":"is of some crash test dummy work that I was doing."},{"time":232000,"text":"Showing how stunts work in different areas, really."},{"time":235000,"text":"And testing breakaway signpost pillars."},{"time":238000,"text":"A company makes a Lattix pillar, which is a network,"},{"time":240000,"text":"a lattice-type pillar that collapses when it's hit."},{"time":243000,"text":"The car on the left drove into the steel pillar."},{"time":246000,"text":"And you can't see it from there, but the engine was in the driver's lap."},{"time":249000,"text":"They did it by remote control."},{"time":251000,"text":"I drove the other one at 60 miles an hour, exactly the same speed,"},{"time":254000,"text":"and clearly walked away from it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257000,"text":"Rolling a car over is another area where we use technology."},{"time":260000,"text":"We used to have to drive up a ramp, and we still do sometimes."},{"time":263000,"text":"But now we have a compressed nitrogen cannon."},{"time":266000,"text":"You can just see, underneath the car, there is a black rod on the floor"},{"time":268000,"text":"by the wheel of the other car."},{"time":270000,"text":"That's the piston that was fired out of the floor."},{"time":272000,"text":"We can flip lorries, coaches, buses, anything over"},{"time":275000,"text":"with a nitrogen cannon with enough power. (Laughs)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"It's a great job, really. (Laughter)"},{"time":282000,"text":"It's such fun!"},{"time":284000,"text":"You should hear"},{"time":286000,"text":"some of the phone conversations that I have with people"},{"time":288000,"text":"on my Bluetooth in the shop."},{"time":290000,"text":"\"Well, we can flip the bus over, we can have it burst into flames,"},{"time":292000,"text":"and how about someone, you know, big explosion.\""},{"time":294000,"text":"And people are looking like this ..."},{"time":296000,"text":"(Laughs)"},{"time":297000,"text":"I sort of forget how bizarre some of those conversations are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300000,"text":"The next thing that I'd like to show you is something that"},{"time":302000,"text":"Dunlop asked me to do earlier this year"},{"time":304000,"text":"with our Channel Five's \"Fifth Gear Show.\""},{"time":306000,"text":"A loop-the-loop, biggest in the world."},{"time":308000,"text":"Only one person had ever done it before."},{"time":310000,"text":"Now, the stuntman solution to this in the old days would be,"},{"time":312000,"text":"\"Let's hit this as fast as possible. 60 miles an hour."},{"time":315000,"text":"Let's just go for it. Foot flat to the floor.\""},{"time":317000,"text":"Well, you'd die if you did that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":319000,"text":"We went to Cambridge University, the other university,"},{"time":321000,"text":"and spoke to a Doctor of Mechanical Engineering there,"},{"time":325000,"text":"a physicist who taught us that it had to be 37 miles an hour."},{"time":328000,"text":"Even then, I caught seven G"},{"time":330000,"text":"and lost a bit of consciousness on the way in."},{"time":333000,"text":"That's a long way to fall, if you get it wrong. That was just about right."},{"time":336000,"text":"So again, science helps us, and with the engineering too --"},{"time":339000,"text":"the modifications to the car and the wheel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"High falls, they're old fashioned stunts."},{"time":343000,"text":"What's interesting about high falls"},{"time":345000,"text":"is that although we use airbags,"},{"time":347000,"text":"and some airbags are quite advanced,"},{"time":350000,"text":"they're designed so you don't slip off the side like you used to,"},{"time":352000,"text":"if you land a bit wrong. So, they're a much safer proposition."},{"time":354000,"text":"Just basically though, it is a basic piece of equipment."},{"time":358000,"text":"It's a bouncy castle"},{"time":360000,"text":"with slats in the side to allow the air to escape."},{"time":362000,"text":"That's all it is, a bouncy castle."},{"time":364000,"text":"That's the only reason we do it. See, it's all fun, this job."},{"time":367000,"text":"What's interesting is we still use cardboard boxes."},{"time":370000,"text":"They used to use cardboard boxes years ago and we still use them."},{"time":373000,"text":"And that's interesting because they are almost retrospective."},{"time":375000,"text":"They're great for catching you, up to certain heights."}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"And on the other side of the fence,"},{"time":380000,"text":"that physical art, the physical performance of the stuntman,"},{"time":384000,"text":"has interfaced with the very highest"},{"time":387000,"text":"technology in I.T. and in software."},{"time":391000,"text":"Not the cardboard box, but the green screen."},{"time":394000,"text":"This is a shot of \"Terminator,\" the movie."},{"time":397000,"text":"Two stunt guys doing what I consider to be a rather benign stunt."},{"time":400000,"text":"It's 30 feet. It's water. It's very simple."},{"time":402000,"text":"With the green screen we can put any background in the world on it,"},{"time":405000,"text":"moving or still,"},{"time":407000,"text":"and I can assure you, nowadays you can't see the joint."},{"time":411000,"text":"This is a parachutist with another parachutist doing exactly the same thing."},{"time":413000,"text":"Completely in the safety of a studio,"},{"time":416000,"text":"and yet with the green screen we can have some moving image that a skydiver took,"},{"time":419000,"text":"and put in the sky moving and the clouds whizzing by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":423000,"text":"Decelerator rigs and wires, we use them a lot."},{"time":426000,"text":"We fly people on wires, like this."},{"time":428000,"text":"This guy is not skydiving. He's being flown like a kite,"},{"time":430000,"text":"or moved around like a kite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"And this is a Guinness World Record attempt."},{"time":436000,"text":"They asked me to open their 50th anniversary show in 2004."},{"time":440000,"text":"And again, technology meant that I could do the fastest abseil over 100 meters,"},{"time":444000,"text":"and stop within a couple of feet of the ground"},{"time":446000,"text":"without melting the rope with the friction,"},{"time":448000,"text":"because of the alloys I used in the descender device."},{"time":451000,"text":"And that's Centre Point in London."},{"time":453000,"text":"We brought Oxford Street and Tottenham Court Road to a standstill."}]},{"cues":[{"time":456000,"text":"Helicopter stunts are always fun,"},{"time":458000,"text":"hanging out of them, whatever."},{"time":461000,"text":"And aerial stunts. No aerial stunt would be the same without skydiving."},{"time":465000,"text":"Which brings us quite nicely to why I'm really here today:"},{"time":468000,"text":"Project Space Jump."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470000,"text":"In 1960, Joseph Kittenger of the United States Air Force"},{"time":473000,"text":"did the most spectacular thing."},{"time":476000,"text":"He did a jump from 100,000 feet, 102,000 to be precise,"},{"time":479000,"text":"and he did it to test high altitude systems"},{"time":482000,"text":"for military pilots"},{"time":484000,"text":"in the new range of aircraft that were going up to 80,000 feet or so."},{"time":487000,"text":"And I'd just like to show you a little footage"},{"time":489000,"text":"of what he did back then."},{"time":491000,"text":"And just how brave he was in 1960, bear in mind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496000,"text":"Project Excelsior, it was called."},{"time":497000,"text":"There were three jumps."},{"time":499000,"text":"They first dropped some dummies."},{"time":503000,"text":"So that's the balloon, big gas balloon."},{"time":505000,"text":"It's that shape because the helium has to expand."},{"time":508000,"text":"My balloon will expand to 500 times"},{"time":511000,"text":"and look like a big pumpkin when it's at the top."},{"time":513000,"text":"These are the dummies being dropped from 100,000 feet,"},{"time":515000,"text":"and there is the camera that's strapped to them."},{"time":517000,"text":"You can clearly see the curvature of the Earth at that kind of altitude."},{"time":521000,"text":"And I'm planning to go from 120,000 feet,"},{"time":524000,"text":"which is about 22 miles."},{"time":526000,"text":"You're in a near vacuum in that environment,"},{"time":528000,"text":"which is in minus 50 degrees."},{"time":531000,"text":"So it's an extremely hostile place to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533000,"text":"This is Joe Kittenger himself."},{"time":535000,"text":"Bear in mind, ladies and gents, this was 1960."},{"time":537000,"text":"He didn't know if he would live or die. This is an extremely brave man."},{"time":540000,"text":"I spoke with him on the phone a few months ago."},{"time":543000,"text":"He's a very humble and wonderful human being."},{"time":545000,"text":"He sent me an email, saying, \"If you get this thing off the ground"},{"time":549000,"text":"I wish you all the best.\" And he signed it, \"Happy landings,\""},{"time":552000,"text":"which I thought was quite lovely."},{"time":554000,"text":"He's in his 80s and he lives in Florida. He's a tremendous guy."},{"time":556000,"text":"This is him in a pressure suit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558000,"text":"Now one of the challenges of going up to altitude is"},{"time":561000,"text":"when you get to 30,000 feet -- it's great, isn't it? --"},{"time":564000,"text":"When you get to 30,000 feet you can really only use oxygen."},{"time":568000,"text":"Above 30,000 feet up to nearly 50,000 feet,"},{"time":571000,"text":"you need pressure breathing, which is where you're wearing a G suit."},{"time":574000,"text":"This is him in his old rock-and-roll jeans there,"},{"time":577000,"text":"pushing him in, those turned up jeans."},{"time":579000,"text":"You need a pressure suit."},{"time":581000,"text":"You need a pressure breathing system"},{"time":583000,"text":"with a G suit that squeezes you, that helps you to breathe in"},{"time":585000,"text":"and helps you to exhale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"Above 50,000 feet you need a space suit, a pressure suit."},{"time":591000,"text":"Certainly at 100,000 feet no aircraft will fly."},{"time":595000,"text":"Not even a jet engine."},{"time":597000,"text":"It needs to be rocket-powered or one of these things,"},{"time":599000,"text":"a great big gas balloon."},{"time":602000,"text":"It took me a while; it took me years to find the right balloon team"},{"time":605000,"text":"to build the balloon that would do this job."},{"time":607000,"text":"I've found that team in America now."},{"time":610000,"text":"And it's made of polyethylene, so it's very thin."},{"time":612000,"text":"We will have two balloons for each of my test jumps,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and two balloons for the main jump, because they"},{"time":617000,"text":"notoriously tear on takeoff."},{"time":619000,"text":"They're just so, so delicate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621000,"text":"This is the step off. He's written on that thing,"},{"time":623000,"text":"\"The highest step in the world.\""},{"time":625000,"text":"And what must that feel like?"},{"time":627000,"text":"I'm excited and I'm scared,"},{"time":630000,"text":"both at the same time in equal measures."},{"time":632000,"text":"And this is the camera that he had on him as he tumbled"},{"time":635000,"text":"before his drogue chute opened to stabilize him."},{"time":638000,"text":"A drogue chute is just a smaller chute which helps to keep your face down."},{"time":641000,"text":"You can just see them there, popping open."},{"time":643000,"text":"Those are the drogue chutes. He had three of them."},{"time":646000,"text":"I did quite a lot of research."},{"time":649000,"text":"And you'll see in a second there, he comes back down to the floor."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653000,"text":"Now just to give you some perspective of this balloon,"},{"time":657000,"text":"the little black dots are people."},{"time":659000,"text":"It's hundreds of feet high. It's enormous."},{"time":661000,"text":"That's in New Mexico."},{"time":663000,"text":"That's the U.S. Air Force Museum."},{"time":665000,"text":"And they've made a dummy of him. That's exactly what it looked like."},{"time":667000,"text":"My gondola will be more simple than that."},{"time":670000,"text":"It's a three sided box, basically."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"So I've had to do quite a lot of training."},{"time":674000,"text":"This is Morocco last year in the Atlas mountains,"},{"time":676000,"text":"training in preparation for some high altitude jumps."},{"time":679000,"text":"This is what the view is going to be like"},{"time":681000,"text":"at 90,000 feet for me."},{"time":683000,"text":"Now you may think this is just"},{"time":685000,"text":"a thrill-seeking trip, a pleasure ride,"},{"time":687000,"text":"just the world's biggest stunt."},{"time":690000,"text":"Well there's a little bit more to it than that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692000,"text":"Trying to find a space suit to do this"},{"time":695000,"text":"has led me to an area of technology"},{"time":698000,"text":"that I never really expected when I set about doing this."},{"time":702000,"text":"I contacted a company in the States"},{"time":704000,"text":"who make suits for NASA."},{"time":706000,"text":"That's a current suit. This was me last year with their chief engineer."},{"time":709000,"text":"That suit would cost me about a million and a half dollars."},{"time":713000,"text":"And it weighs 300 pounds and you can't skydive in it."},{"time":716000,"text":"So I've been stuck. For the past 15 years I've been trying to find a space suit"},{"time":718000,"text":"that would do this job, or someone that will make one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721000,"text":"Something revolutionary happened"},{"time":723000,"text":"a little while ago, at the same facility."},{"time":726000,"text":"That's the prototype of the parachute. I've now had them custom make one,"},{"time":729000,"text":"the only one of its kind in the world. And that's the only suit of its kind in the world."},{"time":732000,"text":"It was made by a Russian that's designed"},{"time":734000,"text":"most of the suits of the past"},{"time":736000,"text":"18 years for the Soviets."},{"time":739000,"text":"He left the company because he saw,"},{"time":741000,"text":"as some other people in the space suit industry,"},{"time":743000,"text":"an emerging market for space suits for space tourists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"You know if you are in an aircraft at 30,000 feet"},{"time":748000,"text":"and the cabin depressurizes, you can have oxygen."},{"time":750000,"text":"If you're at 100,000 feet you die."},{"time":752000,"text":"In six seconds you've lost consciousness. In 10 seconds you're dead."},{"time":755000,"text":"Your blood tries to boil. It's called vaporization."},{"time":757000,"text":"The body swells up. It's awful."},{"time":759000,"text":"And so we expect -- it's not much fun."},{"time":763000,"text":"We expect, and others expect,"},{"time":766000,"text":"that perhaps the FAA, the CAA"},{"time":768000,"text":"might say, \"You need to put someone in a suit"},{"time":770000,"text":"that's not inflated, that's connected to the aircraft.\""},{"time":773000,"text":"Then they're comfortable, they have good vision, like this great big visor."},{"time":776000,"text":"And then if the cabin depressurizes"},{"time":778000,"text":"while the aircraft is coming back down,"},{"time":780000,"text":"in whatever emergency measures, everyone is okay."}]},{"cues":[{"time":782000,"text":"I would like to bring Costa on, if he's here,"},{"time":785000,"text":"to show you the only one of its kind in the world."},{"time":788000,"text":"I was going to wear it,"},{"time":790000,"text":"but I thought I'd get Costa to do it, my lovely assistant."},{"time":792000,"text":"Thank you. He's very hot. Thank you, Costa."},{"time":797000,"text":"This is the communication headset you'll see"},{"time":800000,"text":"on lots of space suits."},{"time":802000,"text":"It's a two-layer suit. NASA suits have got 13 layers."},{"time":806000,"text":"This is a very lightweight suit. It weighs about 15 pounds."},{"time":810000,"text":"It's next to nothing. Especially designed for me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"It's a working prototype. I will use it for all the jumps."},{"time":814000,"text":"Would you just give us a little twirl, please, Costa?"},{"time":817000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":819000,"text":"And it doesn't look far different when it's inflated,"},{"time":821000,"text":"as you can see from the picture down there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823000,"text":"I've even skydived in it in a wind tunnel,"},{"time":826000,"text":"which means that I can practice everything I need to practice, in safety,"},{"time":829000,"text":"before I ever jump out of anything. Thanks very much, Costa."},{"time":831000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":835000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen, that's just about it from me."},{"time":837000,"text":"The status of my mission at the moment"},{"time":839000,"text":"is it still needs a major sponsor."},{"time":841000,"text":"I'm confident that we'll find one."},{"time":843000,"text":"I think it's a great challenge."},{"time":845000,"text":"And I hope that you will agree with me,"},{"time":847000,"text":"it is the greatest stunt on Earth."},{"time":850000,"text":"Thank you very much for your time."},{"time":852000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}